deck: To free the tormented soul of a dead writer, the earth elemental Swamp Thing must travel throught the unfinished tales inside her books which describes alternate worlds and complete them. But is that the real purpose  of this travel? And which are the true intentions of the power behind the writer's dilemma, the powerful Parlament of waves, the water elementals?
description:
The story take place in Swamp thing vol. 2 from issue 151 to issue 158.

It follows how Alec Holland, just after acquire the power of the parliament of stones must help the soul of Anna, a frustrated writer and failed elemental for the parliament of waves,(water elementals), to finish the endings of her stories, compilated in an unfinished book called "River Run".

Swamp thing agree to travel inside the stories, (following the path of the river where Anna's body was found) and finish them. But with each tales, he discovers than the stories say more about him and not about Anna. Must be noted than many of the tales are reminiscence of previous DC alternate universes (earth-X, earth-prime, earth-two) but each one is a twisted tale with alternate versions of the earth elemental.

Eventually the Swamp thing discovers than everything was a ruse: the Parliament of waves was testing him. The water elementals wanted to discover if Holland was worthy of their power.

After confront the parlament, Holland make them free the soul of Anna but only by taking his place as holding the power of the elementals. His path to godhood had started.

description: Cable is drawn to the Everglades when he intercepts a distress call from Lee Forrester. He helps her fight off her attacker, Senyaka. The two then struggle to outrun an approaching hurricane. They are welcomed into a shack and attempt to pass the night, but the two are wracked with painful memories. They learn that their host is the demon D'Spayre who gains nourishment from their suffering. Cable and Lee are able to band together, however, and find hope. With D'Spayre defeated, Belasco presents himself and coerces Cable to help him fight against S'ym, a demon that wants the Nexus of All Realities to consume the Earth. Cable fights S'ym and wins. Belasco is able to shut the Nexus down and Cable and Lee are able to get back to their lives.

description:
Crazy Dave goes on an inventing spree, distracting the plants, who move out to the old family mansion. Patrice and Nate try to give them advice on housekeeping and living in human culture. Zomboss finds out where they are, and decides to try to do a better job of living among humans. The zombies infiltrate the house and insert video cameras, so he can learn from the kids' lessons.

The plants continue to have difficulty acting like people. Patrice and Nate start an incentive program that starts to help. Zomboss tries to replicate this by giving the zombies pictures of himself. Both groups continue to train. They go into town in disguise to see if humans will notice them. The two groups meet and try to not give themselves away by fighting. They have a contest to act human, which ends in a tie.

They return home, but later end up in a battle. Nate and Patrice don't understand why their plans aren't working--it's because Zomboss has been watching them make their plans over the video cameras. They take a break and find the cameras, then block them with anti-gravity goldfish that Dave invented earlier. Nate and Patrice disguise themselves as zombies and infiltrate Zomboss's headquarters, putting in their own cameras.

Zomboss starts a zombie parade. Dave, who loves parade, joins in. They have another contest. Things look bad for the plants, but when Patrice points out that Nigel, Frogpants, and Tugboat have been stealing Zomboss's Pop Smarts (which they saw on their video cameras), the zombies turn on themselves, and lose the day.

deck: A flash-forward story into the not-so-distant post-apocalyptic and dystopian future of Bloodshot and the Valiant Universe.
description:
The Analog Man is set in a not-too-distant post-apocalyptic future, Bloodshot & Magic have found a quiet life in a village out in the desert. Food and water supply is scarce and Bloodshot has to do water runs every now and then. These runs see him drive through the desert that is controlled by the Shadowmen and fill a huge tank near the walls of Future-L.A., a dystopian city where the rich and wealthy people live. The city is controlled by X-O sentries and some A.I. of sorts called "Goo Tech."

While Bloodshot, a.k.a. the Analog Man, tries to live a normal life disguising himself as an old man, these water runs always have him switch back into Bloodshot. While the nanites that run through his body seem to be outdated and inferior to the more advanced Goo-Tech, he has managed to use them for cloaking an entire truck thus making it invisible for the X-O sentries as there is no other way to get to the water supplies of Future-L.A. otherwise.
name: The Analog Man
